1 AN ACT relating to economic development.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 ïƒ¢Section 1. KRS 154.12-205 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) There is hereby created an independent, de jure corporation of the Commonwealth
5 with all the general corporate powers incidental thereto which shall be known as the
6 "Bluegrass State Skills Corporation." The corporation shall be a political
7 subdivision of the state and shall be attached to the Cabinet for Economic
8 Development.
9 (2) The corporation is created and established to improve and promote the employment
10 opportunities of the citizens of the Commonwealth by creating and expanding
11 programs of skills training and education which meet the needs of qualified
12 companies.
13 (3) The corporation shall be governed by a board of directors consisting of seventeen
14 (17) members, including the following five (5) ex officio members: the
15 commissioner of the Department of Workforce Development or his or her designee,
16 the secretary of the Cabinet for Economic Development, the secretary of the
17 Education and Labor Cabinet, the president of the Council on Postsecondary
18 Education, and the president of the Kentucky Community and Technical College
19 System. The twelve (12) other members shall be appointed by the Governor,
20 including persons having knowledge and experience in business and industry, skills
21 training, education, and minority employment; and at least one (1) of the twelve
22 (12) members shall be appointed to represent labor organizations. Each member
23 appointed by the Governor shall serve for a term of four (4) years, except that in
24 making the initial appointments, the Governor shall appoint three (3) members to
25 serve for one (1) year, three (3) members to serve for two (2) years, three (3)
26 members to serve for three (3) years, and three (3) members to serve for four (4)
27 years. All succeeding appointments shall be for a term of four (4) years.
