1 (4) In the event of a vacancy, the Governor may appoint a replacement member who
2 shall hold office during the remainder of the term so vacated.
3 (5) Any member may be removed from his or her appointment by the Governor for
4 cause.
5 (6) The Governor shall designate a member of the board as its chairman.
6 (7) Members of the board of directors of the corporation, except for ex officio
7 members, shall be entitled to compensation for their services in the amount of one
8 hundred dollars ($100) for each regular or special called meeting of the corporation,
9 and all members shall be entitled to reimbursement for any actual and necessary
10 expenses incurred in the performance of their duties.
11 (8) The board of directors of the corporation shall annually elect a vice chairman, a
12 secretary, and a treasurer. The secretary shall keep a record of the proceedings of
13 the corporation and shall be custodian of all books, documents, and papers filed
14 with the corporation, and its official seal.
15 (9) The Cabinet for Economic Development shall provide staff and support services to
16 the corporation and shall direct and supervise its administrative affairs and general
17 management subject to the policies, control, and direction of the board.
18 (10) All officers and employees of the corporation having access to its funding shall give
19 bond to the corporation, at its expense, in the amount and with the surety as the
20 board may prescribe.
